Instead of spreading the = statement everywhere, is it possible to simply use PidCore as the data structure to wrap all these variables? And then, logging is just simply copying/referencing  this data structure.

For instance:

struct Data{int a; float b;};

void func(){
    Data data;
    data.a = getA() + magic;
    data.b = getB() - magic;
    log(data);
}

We could just use https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/locale/isalnum and set the locale to compare to if we're worried about that:

```
std::locale loc1("C");
std::isalnum(c, loc1);
```
